<title type="html"><![CDATA[OS-Native table widget]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="https://forums.whatwg.org/bb3/viewtopic.php?t=121&amp;p=477#p477"><![CDATA[
It is feasable to create a table in Javascript to list information, to resize columns and to sort it without reloading the page, with much code and bloat (sluggish), but if I could create a table like this easily in HTML with no Javascript, and with the table headers with the same look &amp; feel as the OS I'm using that would be great:<br /><br /><img src="http://www.imgplace.com/directory/dir3517/1196818194.png" alt="Image" /><br /><br />We could use very similar markup as the &lt;table&gt;, &lt;th&gt;, &lt;tr&gt;, and &lt;td&gt; tags, just make it more dynamic:<br /><ul><li> Resizable columns</li><li> Sortable columns</li><li> OS-native header look and feel</li><li> Append data preview with three dots when the data doesn't fit the cell (kind of like &quot;overflow: hidden&quot;)</li></ul><br /><br />We could for instance use this feature in webmail applications's lists of messages to make them more usable, faster, and easier to code (UI).<br />What do you think?<br /><br /><img src="https://forums.whatwg.org/bb3/images/smilies/icon_smile.gif" alt=":)" title="Smile" /><p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="https://forums.whatwg.org/bb3/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=202">calande</a> — Wed Dec 05, 2007 1:35 am</p><hr />
